Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities are represented by the Total Current Liabilities since no non-current liabilities are separately provided.  
  Total Liabilities = 2,110,671.05  
• Total Owner's Equity = 14,103,190.60  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity = 2,110,671.05 / 14,103,190.60 ≈ 0.15

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit = 1,103,190.60  
• Total Revenue = 5,813,420.67  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (1,103,190.60 / 5,813,420.67) × 100 ≈ 18.97%

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 1,598,438.00  
• Total Current Liabilities = 2,110,671.05  
• Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Total Current Liabilities = 1,598,438.00 / 2,110,671.05 ≈ 0.76

Thus, the answer is:
